cs.HCI, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper is about developing a programming model for interactive visualizations, which involves handling user interactions, background data processing, remote requests, and streaming data. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI). The paper also discusses declarative programming, which involves specifying what the state of the interface should be as queries over event history, which could fall under Database (cs.DB) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions resolving conflicts from concurrent processes, which is a common issue in Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
